                <h1 id="InspirationText" style="margin-bottom: 5rem;">Inspiration</h1>
                <p>
                    When we first heard about iGEM, we also heard about the wonders of synthetic biology, and were more
                    than
                    inspired by the projects we read about. Learning about all the things that had been done only
                    reaffirmed
                    the notion that not even the sky was our limit. So what better idea than to use all these incredible
                    tools to solve a real world issue in such a way that we could notice an impact in our own community?
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-12">
                <p>
                    When we first heard about iGEM, we also heard about the wonders of synthetic biology, and were more
                    than
                    inspired by the projects we read about. Learning about all the thing that had been done only
                    reaffirmed
                    the notion that not even the sky was our limit. So, what better idea than to use all these
                    incredible
                    tools to solve a real-world issue in such a way that we could notice and impact in our own
                    community.
                </p>

                <p>
                    Our team is comprised of people who have lived most of their lives in the state of Chihuahua.
                    Knowing
                    our home and our people for so many years and in so many different aspects, we wanted to do
                    something
                    that would truly influence our community. We wanted to create a meaningful change in our
                    surroundings.
                </p>

                <p>
                    Before being part of iGEM Tec-Chihuahua 2019, some our team members had the chance to meet and work
                    with
                    people immersed in the rural area, while others had developed small research projects in our school
                    regarding agronomic issues; somehow all of us had some sort of experience with agriculture and its
                    importance for Mexican people.
                </p>

                <p>
                    Four our country, agriculture fulfills the nutritional needs of millions of citizens, preserves
                    natural
                    environments, stimulates progress by improving the quality of life in rural areas, and has also been
                    ingrained in our culture and traditions since the very beginning.<sup><a href="#absRef7">1</a></sup>
                </p>

                <p>
                    A certain concern seemed to stand out among the people our team members knew and had worked with.
                    Both
                    agronomic engineers and crop producers involved in the cotton agricultural business, mentioned
                    <i>Verticillium</i>, a phytopathogenic fungus that wilts their crops and has only worsened with
                    every new
                    season. This particular disease has been on of their major problems for more than 7 years, and still
                    they haven’t received any help about this whatsoever. This year the overall production is expected
                    to
                    lower considerably compared to previous seasons. One of the principal measures agricultors use as an
                    attempt to control this situation is applying great amounts of agrochemicals; representing a hazard
                    regarding soil, water and air pollution.
                </p>

                <p>
                    Unfortunately, so far there is no product or efficient treatment to deal with this fungal infection.
                    Besides, the lack of proper methods to detect this disease in its earliest stages represent another
                    crucial concern.
                </p>

                <p>
                    Due to the above, we do believe that through synthetic biology we can reach a solution to the
                    inhibition
                    of <i>V. dahliae</i>, support of the most important sector of our region by improving the production
                    amount
                    and
                    preserving this valuable product that our state and our country produce and reducing fungicide
                    pollution
                    in consequence of toxic chemical components, in addition to help to decrease the suicide rate
                    because of
                    them.
                </p>

            </div>
        </div>
